Package: frameR
Type: Package
Title: Measuring Emphasis Frames in Political Text Using Sentence Embeddings
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(
      given   = "Spencer",
      family  = "Corp",
      email   = "spenccorp2@gmail.com",
      role    = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Provides tools for measuring emphasis frames in political text
    using transformer-based sentence embeddings and cosine similarity.
    Frames are operationalized as semantic associations between issue-relevant
    discourse and theoretically specified frame category keywords, following
    Druckman (2011). The package implements a four-step pipeline: embedding
    a corpus, identifying issue-relevant sentences, specifying and embedding
    frame categories, and measuring frame strength with bootstrap uncertainty
    quantification and permutation-based significance testing. Designed for
    cross-national and cross-lingual comparative research, the package
    accepts any sentence embedding model and includes utilities for
    domain adaptation. Accompanies the methods paper introducing the
    approach.
